cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper is about automatic speech recognition (ASR) using deep neural networks (DNNs) and recurrent neural networks (RNNs), which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) tasks.
- cs.SD (Sound) is also a likely category as the paper deals with speech signals and their processing.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category as the paper involves training and optimizing neural networks for ASR.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as ASR is a subfield of AI and the paper presents a new framework for building ASR systems.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible category as the paper focuses on deep neural networks and their application in ASR.
